  <thing id="fExArmProf" name="Exotic Armor Proficiency" description="Choose a type of exotic armor, such as mammoth leather or tumbler&#146;s breastplate. You understand how to wear that type of exotic armor properly.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: Armor Proficiency of the appropriate sort (for example, you must have Armor Proficiency [light] to take Exotic Armor Proficiency [mammoth leather]).\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: You are proficient with a specific type of exotic armor and take no armor non proficiency penalties when you wear it (see Table 7&#150;2: Armor and Shields, page 158).\n\n{b}Normal{/b}: A character who is wearing armor with which she is not proficient applies its armor check penalty on attack rolls and on all Strength- and Dexterity-based ability checks and skill checks.\n\n{b}Special{/b}: You can gain this feat multiple times. Each time you take the feat, it applies to a new type of exotic armor. A fighter may select Exotic Armor Proficiency as one of his fighter bonus feats (see page 38 of the Player&#146;s Handbook).\n\n{i}Note{/i}: This feat originally appeared in the FORGOTTEN REALMS&#174; game supplement Underdark. This version of the feat supersedes the previous version." compset="Feat">
    <comment>Pre req (Done)

Get the Scripts from the Test versions (Done)

Erase the Tests (Done)</comment>
