  <thing id="fMountWarr" name="Mountain Warrior" description="You are adept at fighting on the uneven ground of mountainous terrain.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: Survival 5 ranks, base attack bonus +3.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: When you make a melee attack from higher ground than your opponent, you gain a +1 bonus on your damage roll. When you make a ranged attack from higher ground than your target, you gain a +1 bonus on your attack roll.\n\nWhen an opponent attacks you in melee from higher ground, the opponent does not gain a +1 bonus on its attack roll.\n\nYou gain a +2 bonus on all Balance checks made when moving on steep slopes (see page 89 of the Dungeon Master&#146;s Guide).\n\n{b}Normal{/b}: A character who makes melee attacks from higher ground gains a +1 bonus on attack rolls. Ranged attacks made from higher ground do not receive any bonus.\n\n{b}Special{/b}: A fighter may select Mountain Warrior as one of his fighter bonus feats (see page 38 of the Player&#146;s Handbook)." compset="Feat" summary="+1 melee dam/+1 rng att if higher, deny foe melee att bon. +2 to balance ck on slopes." uniqueness="useronce">
