  <thing id="cRsmRunMag" name="Rune Magic" description="A runesmith Learns to prepare his arcane spells as runes inscribed on solid objects (usually tablets of stone, but others are possible). He prepares spells as normal, except that instead of readying the spells in his mind, he readies them in the form of runes. Preparing daily spells takes about the same amount of time as normal preparation and requires the same amount of the rest beforehand. A runesmith can leave spell slots unprepared to scribe runes at a later time, just as a wizard can leave spell slots unprepared and fill them later.\nA runesmith who casts a spell prepared in rune form can cast it without any somatic component. however, all spells cast from rune form automatically have a material component (the rune itself). In casting the spell, the rune is erased from the tablet, just as a spell cast normally by a wizardis erased from his mind. A runesmith cannot get around the runic material component by the means of an ability or feat such as eschew materials, although he can use such feats and abilities to waive any other material components for a spell he prepares in rune form, subject to the limitations of the ability.\nIn all other ways, spells prepared in rune form are treated identically to normal spells.\nA runesmith may prepare and use spells in the normal fashion should he so desire." compset="ClSpecial" summary="prepare spells using runes (as still spell)">
    <usesource source="srcRoS"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpRsm"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="SpecUp"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Extra"/>
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="1"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cRsmStonEx" name="Stonecraft Expertise" description="Beginning at 2nd level, a runesmith gains a bonus equal to his class level on Appraise and Craft checks related to objects made of stone." compset="ClSpecial" summary="gain bonus equal to class level on appraise and craft checks for">
    <usesource source="srcRoS"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpRsm"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="SpecUp"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Extra"/>
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="2"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cRsmShrRun" name="Share Runes" description="At 3rd level and higher,  a runesmith can prepare a limited number of rune-form arcane spells such that they can be activated (cast) by any character. The spell&apos;s casting time Remains the same, and it is just as effective as a spell cast by the runesmith himself. the spell&apos;s level is increased by two, much as if a metamagic feat had been applied to it.\nA runesmith can prepare a maximum number of shareable runes each day equal to his Constitution modifier (minimum 1). Each time this ability is used to prepare a shareable rune, that rune takes up one of the runesmiths available spell slots for that day." compset="ClSpecial" summary="Create rune-spells usable by others at +2 spell level">
    <usesource source="srcRoS"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="SpecUp"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpRsm"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Extra"/>
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="3"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cRsmPerRun" name="Permanent Rune" description="A 5th-level runesmith knows the secret of inscribing a single permanent rune of a single chosen spell into his flesh. To inscribe a permanent rune, a runesmith must permanently sacrifice an arcane spell slot of one level higher than the spell to be inscribed as a permanent rune, and spend 24 hours inscribing the rune. if the spell has a costly material component, he must expend resources equal to 20 times the GP cost of the material component. If it has a costly focus, he must expend resources equal to the cost of the focus. if the spell has an XP cost, he must spend the XP as if he had cast the spell normally.\n\nOnce he has inscribed a spell as a premanent rune, a runesmith can activate the chosen spell as a spell-like ability (using his arcane caster level as the caster level) twice per day." compset="ClSpecial" summary="Permanently mark 1 rune on self, gain spell-like ability 2/day">
    <usesource source="srcRoS"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpRsm"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="SpecUp"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Extra"/>
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="5"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="sClrEarHam" name="Earth Hammer" description="You infuse one melee weapon with the power of the earth. The base damage of the weapon improves by one step (as if the weapon were one size category larger). Regardless of the weapon&#146;s normal material and damage type, the weapon deals bludgeoning damage and overcomes damage reduction as if it were made of adamantine.\n\nIf this spell is cast on a weapon made of a different special material (such as alchemical silver), the properties of that material are replaced with those of adamantine for the duration of the spell." compset="Spell" summary="Improve base damage of target weapon by one category.">
