    </thing>
  <thing id="cDCSmGiant" name="Smite Giants" description="A dwarf cleric who takes the 1st-level racial substitution level can attempt to smite a giant with a melee attack, similar to the way a paladin smites an evil creature. She adds her Constitution bonus (if any) to her attack roll and deals an extra 1 point of damage per cleric level. The cleric can use this ability a number of times per day equal to 1 + her Con modifier (minimum once per day). If the cleric accidentally smites a creature that is not a giant, the smite has no effect but still counts as one of the cleric&#146;s daily smite attempts." compset="ClSpecial">
    <usesource source="srcRoS"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Super"/>
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="1"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowCharge"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpClr"/>
    <eval phase="PostAttr" priority="10000"><![CDATA[var uses as number
var attbon as number
var dambon as number

~ Set charges
uses = 1 + hero.child[aCON].field[aModBonus].value
uses = maximum(1,uses)

field[hTotal].value = uses

~Set attack and damage bonus, indicate in summary

attbon = maximum(0,hero.child[aCON].field[aModBonus].value)
dambon = #levelcount[Cleric]

field[xSumm].text = "Add Con bonus (+" & attbon & ") to attack and Cleric level (+" & dambon & ") to damage against giants."]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cvDwClr4" name="Dwarf Cleric" description="The dwarf cleric dedicates herself to her clan and the forge. She takes an active role in defending her people, often serving on the front lines of a battle. In exchange for greater martial ability and power when casting spells of the earth, the cleric gives up her ability to turn or rebuke undead and some of her spellcasting prowess.\n\n{b}Hit Die:{/b} d10\n\nDwarf cleric substitution levels have the class skills of the standard cleric class plus Knowledge (dungeoneering) (Int).\n\nThis racial substitution level is only available to dwarf clerics who follow Moradin (or any other deity whose favored weapon is a warhammer).\n\nAt 4th level, the Dwarf Cleric gains the ability Hammer Specialist. This benefit replaces the 2nd-level spell slot gained by a standard cleric at 4th level. From now on, the cleric can prepare one fewer 2nd-level cleric spell than indicated on Table 3&#150;6, page 31 of the Player&#146;s Handbook." compset="ClassVary" uniqueness="unique">
