    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Extra"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cvDwFtr8" name="Dwarf Fighter" description="The prototypical image of dwarfhood is the heavily armored fighter. Many dwarves pursue this class, and most multiclass dwarves have at least a single level of fighter to augment their abilities.\n\nThe dwarf fighter gives up versatility to specialize in the arts of war most needed in dwarf communities. He focuses on traditional fighting styles and takes advantage of the dwarf&#146;s lack of mobility.\n\n{b}Hit Die:{/b} d12\n\nDwarf fighter substitution levels have the class skills of the standard fighter class plus Knowledge (dungeoneering) (Int).\n\nAt 8th level, a Dwarf Fighter gains Heavy Armor Optimization. This benefit replaces the bonus feat gained by a standard 8th-level fighter." compset="ClassVary" uniqueness="unique">
