  <thing id="cvDwSor1" name="Dwarf Sorcerer" description="In most dwarf communities, sorcerers are relatively rare. Dwarves don&#146;t tend to have the force of personality required for top-notch sorcerers; thus they often prefer wizardry instead. However, a dwarf sorcerer can tap into other reservoirs of power&#151;including the very earth itself&#151;to enhance his arcane aptitude. To do this, he gives up some of his versatility, but the power gained is substantial.\n\n{b}Hit Die:{/b} d6\n\nDwarf sorcerer substitution levels have the class skills of the standard sorcerer class plus Knowledge (dungeoneering) (Int).\n\nAt 1st level, a Dwarf Sorcerer gains Arcane Earthbound. This benefit replaces the standard sorcerer&#146;s ability to gain a familiar. If the dwarf gains a familiar from another class (such as wizard), his sorcerer levels don&#146;t stack to determine the familiar&#146;s abilities." compset="ClassVary" uniqueness="unique">
    <fieldval field="cvLevel" value="1"/>
    <fieldval field="cvHitDice" value="6"/>
    <fieldval field="cvArcFStar" value="-1"/>
