var bonus as number

bonus = hero.child[aCON].field[aModBonus].value
bonus = maximum(0,bonus)

hero.child[cHelpSor].field[cSplAttBon].value += bonus</eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cvDwSor9" name="Dwarf Sorcerer" description="In most dwarf communities, sorcerers are relatively rare. Dwarves don&#146;t tend to have the force of personality required for top-notch sorcerers; thus they often prefer wizardry instead. However, a dwarf sorcerer can tap into other reservoirs of power&#151;including the very earth itself&#151;to enhance his arcane aptitude. To do this, he gives up some of his versatility, but the power gained is substantial.\n\n{b}Hit Die:{/b} d6\n\nDwarf sorcerer substitution levels have the class skills of the standard sorcerer class plus Knowledge (dungeoneering) (Int).\n\nAt 9th level, a Dwarf Sorcerer gains Earth Meditation. This benefit replaces the standard sorcerer&#146;s ability to learn a new 4th-level spell at 9th level. From now on, the dwarf sorcerer&#146;s number of 4th-level spells known is one fewer than the value shown on Table 3&#150;17, page 54 of the Player&#146;s Handbook." compset="ClassVary" uniqueness="unique">
