  <thing id="cGDEleCom" name="Elemental Companion" description="A goliath druid who takes the 6th-level racial substitution level can imbue her animal companion with the power of elemental earth. The animal companion&#146;s Strength increases by 2, and its Dexterity is reduced by 2. Its natural armor bonus increases by 3. It gains a burrow speed of 10 feet (or, if it has a burrow speed, that speed increases by 10 feet). The companion gains the earth mastery extraordinary ability (+1 bonus on attack rolls and damage rolls if both it and its foe touch the ground; if an opponent is airborne or waterborne, the earth companion takes a &#150;4 penalty on attack rolls and damage rolls). It also gains damage reduction 5/magic as an extraordinary ability.\n\nThe companion&#146;s type doesn&#146;t change, but it gains the earth subtype. \n\nIf a goliath druid replaces her animal companion with a new one, she can apply this effect to the new companion, but only if the reduction in her effective druid level reduction would not make the new companion unavailable to her. The previous companion loses the special abilities when it leaves the druid.\n\nFor the purpose of determining her animal companion&#146;s bonus Hit Dice, special abilities, and so on, the effective level of the goliath druid who selects this substitution level is reduced by three, per the Alternate Animal Companions table on page 36 of the {i}Player&#146;s Handbook{/i}." compset="ClSpecial" summary="Imbue your companion with the power of elemental earth.">
    <usesource source="srcRoS"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpDrd"/>
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="6"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Extra"/>
    <tag group="User" tag="GolEleComp" name="Goliath Druid Elemental Companion"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ClExLose"/>
    <eval phase="First" priority="50" index="3">perform hero.childfound[cAnimComp].minion[AnimComp].assign[User.GolEleComp]</eval>
    <eval phase="First" priority="98" index="4">hero.childfound[cAnimComp].minion[AnimComp].child[xBurrow2].field[Value].value += 10</eval>
    <eval phase="First" priority="498">hero.childfound[cAnimClass].field[CompClLev].value -= 3

hero.childfound[cAnimComp].minion[AnimComp].child[aSTR].field[aNormMod].value += 2

hero.childfound[cAnimComp].minion[AnimComp].child[aDEX].field[aNormMod].value -= 2

hero.childfound[cAnimComp].minion[AnimComp].child[ArmorClass].field[tACNatural].value += 3</eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cvGoDrd12" name="Goliath Druid" description="The goliath race venerates nature in its various forms, and druids are the most prominent spellcasters, divine or otherwise, among goliath tribes. Goliath druids forge particularly strong bonds with the earth and stone of their environment, granting them and their animal companions unusual powers related to elemental earth.\n\n{b}Hit Die:{/b} d8\n\nAt 12th level, a Goliath Druid gains Wild Shape (earth). This benefit replaces the standard druid&#146;s 12th-level wild shape (plant) ability." compset="ClassVary" uniqueness="unique">
